{
  "texts": [
    "By directly engaging older adults in the design process, researchers gain valuable insights into their preferences, needs, and concerns, enabling them to develop studies and activities that are tailored to their specific circumstances, interests, and abilities.",
    "This participatory approach not only enhances the relevance and effectiveness of research but also fosters a more inclusive and empowering research environment that recognizes older adults as active partners in research rather than mere subjects.",
    "While the involvement of older adults in our review was relatively low, the impact of participatory design was evident in studies that employed this approach [69,83,123,124,129,134].",
    "These studies demonstrated higher effectiveness rates compared to those that did not involve older adults in the design process.",
    "These findings underscore the significance of a co-creation approach throughout the study design and implementation phases."
  ]
}